[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      2[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      3[0m:[38;5;10m[49m > **Heads up:** This is a deliberately simple, illustrative implementation of the pseudocode walkthrough from Recipe 8.3. It shows one way you could translate those concepts into working Python using boto3. It is not production-ready. Think of it as the sketchpad version: useful for understanding how the pieces fit together, not something you'd wire into a CDI workflow on Monday morning. Consider it a starting point, not a destination.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      4[0m:[38;5;10m[49m >
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      5[0m:[38;5;10m[49m > The main recipe describes a Lambda-backed API Gateway architecture. This example implements the same logic as a callable function you can run locally against the Comprehend Medical API. The extraction, filtering, and coding rule logic is identical to what you'd deploy in Lambda. The difference is operational plumbing, not core logic.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      6[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      7[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      8[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      9[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Setup
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     10[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     11[0m:[38;5;10m[49m You'll need the AWS SDK for Python:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     12[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     13[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```bash
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     14[0m:[38;5;10m[49m pip install boto3
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     15[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     16[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     17[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Your environment needs credentials configured (via environment variables, an instance profile, or `~/.aws/credentials`). The IAM role or user needs:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     18[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `comprehend:InferICD10CM`
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     19[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `dynamodb:PutItem`
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     20[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `dynamodb:GetItem`
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     21[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `dynamodb:Query`
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     22[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     23[0m:[38;5;10m[49m No BAA-covered data in development. Use synthetic clinical notes only. The MIMIC-III dataset on PhysioNet provides de-identified clinical text if you need realistic content for testing.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     24[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     25[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     26[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     27[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Configuration and Constants
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     28[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     29[0m:[38;5;10m[49m These live at the top of the module. Thresholds, rules, and table names are configuration, not logic. You'll tune these as your coders provide feedback on suggestion quality.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     30[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     31[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     32[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import logging
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     33[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import json
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     34[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import datetime
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     35[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from datetime import timezone
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     36[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from decimal import Decimal
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     37[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     38[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import boto3
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     39[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from botocore.config import Config
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     40[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     41[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Structured logging. Never log PHI (patient names, MRNs, note text).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     42[0m:[38;5;10m[49m logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     43[0m:[38;5;10m[49m logger.setLevel(logging.INFO)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     44[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     45[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Adaptive retry handles Comprehend Medical throttling gracefully.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     46[0m:[38;5;10m[49m BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG = Config(retries={"max_attempts": 3, "mode": "adaptive"})
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     47[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     48[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # boto3 clients at module level for Lambda container reuse.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     49[0m:[38;5;10m[49m comprehend_medical = boto3.client("comprehendmedical", config=BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     50[0m:[38;5;10m[49m dynamodb = boto3.resource("dynamodb")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     51[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     52[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # --- Thresholds ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     53[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     54[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Minimum confidence score to include a code suggestion.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     55[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Low on purpose: we want recall. The coder filters from here.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     56[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # If suggestions feel too noisy, raise this to 0.40-0.50.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     57[0m:[38;5;10m[49m CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD = 0.30
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     58[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     59[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Maximum suggestions to return. Top N by confidence.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     60[0m:[38;5;10m[49m MAX_SUGGESTIONS = 15
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     61[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     62[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Comprehend Medical's per-request character limit.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     63[0m:[38;5;10m[49m MAX_TEXT_LENGTH = 20_000
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     64[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     65[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # --- DynamoDB Tables ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     66[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     67[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Stores suggestion results for audit and feedback collection.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     68[0m:[38;5;10m[49m SUGGESTIONS_TABLE = "icd10-suggestions"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     69[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     70[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Stores coding rules: specificity overrides, combination codes, excludes pairs.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     71[0m:[38;5;10m[49m RULES_TABLE = "icd10-coding-rules"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     72[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     73[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # --- Section Priority ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     74[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Clinical note sections most relevant for diagnosis coding.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     75[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Assessment/Plan is where physicians state diagnostic conclusions.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     76[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # HPI describes the current episode. These drive coding decisions.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     77[0m:[38;5;10m[49m PRIORITY_SECTIONS = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     78[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "assessment and plan",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     79[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "assessment",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     80[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "impression",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     81[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "discharge diagnosis",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     82[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "hospital course",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     83[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "hpi",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     84[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "history of present illness",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     85[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     86[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     87[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     88[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     89[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     90[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 1: Preprocess the Clinical Note
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     91[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     92[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *Maps to the pseudocode's `preprocess_note(raw_note_text)`. Clinical notes have structure: sections with headers. Not all sections are equally useful for coding. Assessment and Plan drives most diagnosis codes. Review of Systems and Past Medical History add noise that dilutes suggestion accuracy. This step segments the note and prioritizes the sections that matter.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     93[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     94[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     95[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def preprocess_note(raw_note_text: str) -> str:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     96[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     97[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Segment a clinical note by section headers and reorder so that
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     98[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     high-value sections (Assessment/Plan, HPI) appear first.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     99[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    100[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Clinical notes typically use ALL CAPS or title-cased lines followed
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    101[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     by colons as section headers. The exact format varies by EHR vendor
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    102[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     and documentation template. This parser handles the common patterns.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    103[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    104[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    105[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         raw_note_text: Full clinical note text as received from the EHR.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    106[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    107[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    108[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Reordered note text, truncated to Comprehend Medical's limit.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    109[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Priority sections appear first so they're never lost to truncation.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    110[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    111[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Split on lines that look like section headers.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    112[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Common patterns: "ASSESSMENT AND PLAN:", "Assessment and Plan:", "A/P:"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    113[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # This is intentionally simple. Production systems use regex or
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    114[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # EHR-specific section parsers (many EHRs expose structured sections via FHIR).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    115[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     lines = raw_note_text.split("\n")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    116[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     sections = {}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    117[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     current_section = "preamble"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    118[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     current_content = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    119[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    120[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for line in lines:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    121[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         stripped = line.strip()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    122[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Heuristic: a line that's mostly uppercase, ends with colon, or
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    123[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # is a known section name is treated as a header.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    124[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if stripped.endswith(":") and len(stripped) < 60 and stripped.upper() == stripped:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    125[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Save previous section
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    126[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if current_content:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    127[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 sections[current_section] = "\n".join(current_content)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    128[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             current_section = stripped.rstrip(":").lower()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    129[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             current_content = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    130[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    131[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             current_content.append(line)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    132[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    133[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Don't forget the last section
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    134[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if current_content:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    135[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         sections[current_section] = "\n".join(current_content)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    136[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    137[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Build output: priority sections first, then everything else.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    138[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     priority_text = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    139[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     remaining_text = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    140[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    141[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for section_name in PRIORITY_SECTIONS:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    142[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if section_name in sections:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    143[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             priority_text.append(sections[section_name])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    144[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    145[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for section_name, content in sections.items():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    146[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if section_name not in PRIORITY_SECTIONS:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    147[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             remaining_text.append(content)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    148[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    149[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     combined = "\n\n".join(priority_text + remaining_text)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    150[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    151[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Truncate to API limit. Priority content is safe because it's first.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    152[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if len(combined) > MAX_TEXT_LENGTH:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    153[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         combined = combined[:MAX_TEXT_LENGTH]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    154[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         logger.info("Note truncated from %d to %d characters", len(raw_note_text), MAX_TEXT_LENGTH)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    155[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    156[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return combined
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    157[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    158[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    159[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    160[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    161[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 2: Call Comprehend Medical InferICD10CM
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    162[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    163[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *Maps to the pseudocode's `get_icd10_suggestions(clinical_text)`. This is the core extraction call. InferICD10CM takes clinical text and returns medical condition entities, each with ranked ICD-10-CM code candidates and confidence scores. It handles negation detection, contextual inference, and multi-entity extraction in a single API call. One call does the work of an entire NLP pipeline: entity detection, assertion classification, and code mapping.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    164[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    165[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    166[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def get_icd10_suggestions(clinical_text: str) -> list:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    167[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    168[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Call Amazon Comprehend Medical's InferICD10CM API.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    169[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    170[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The API returns a list of medical condition entities found in the text.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    171[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Each entity includes:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    172[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       - Text: the span that triggered detection ("Type 2 diabetes")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    173[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       - Category: always MEDICAL_CONDITION for this API
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    174[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       - Traits: list of attributes (NEGATION, DIAGNOSIS, SIGN, SYMPTOM, etc.)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    175[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       - ICD10CMConcepts: ranked list of code suggestions with confidence scores
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    176[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    177[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The API handles negation internally. "Patient denies chest pain" will still
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    178[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return an entity for "chest pain" but it will have the NEGATION trait, which
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    179[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     we filter on in Step 3.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    180[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    181[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    182[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         clinical_text: Preprocessed note text (output of preprocess_note).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    183[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    184[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    185[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         List of entity dicts from the API response.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    186[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    187[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response = comprehend_medical.infer_icd10_cm(Text=clinical_text)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    188[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    189[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Response structure:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    190[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    191[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     #   "Entities": [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    192[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     #     {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    193[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     #       "Id": 0,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    194[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     #       "Text": "Type 2 diabetes",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    195[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     #       "Category": "MEDICAL_CONDITION",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    196[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     #       "Type": "DX_NAME",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    197[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     #       "Score": 0.95,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    198[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     #       "BeginOffset": 142,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    199[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     #       "EndOffset": 158,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    200[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     #       "Traits": [{"Name": "DIAGNOSIS", "Score": 0.93}],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    201[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     #       "ICD10CMConcepts": [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    202[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     #         {"Code": "E11.9", "Description": "Type 2 diabetes mellitus without complications", "Score": 0.82},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     #         {"Code": "E11.65", "Description": "Type 2 diabetes mellitus with hyperglycemia", "Score": 0.71},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     #         ...
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    205[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     #       ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    206[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     #     },
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    207[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     #     ...
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    208[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     #   ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    209[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    211[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     entities = response.get("Entities", [])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("InferICD10CM returned %d entities", len(entities))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return entities
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 3: Filter and Score Suggestions
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *Maps to the pseudocode's `filter_and_score(entities)`. Not every entity should become a suggestion. Negated conditions (documented as absent), hypothetical mentions, and family history references need to be excluded or handled separately. This step applies clinical logic to transform raw API output into a clean suggestion list.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def filter_and_score(entities: list) -> list:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Filter Comprehend Medical entities and build a ranked suggestion list.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Filtering logic:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       - Exclude entities with NEGATION trait (documented as absent)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       - Exclude entities below the confidence threshold
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       - Deduplicate codes (keep highest confidence instance)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       - Sort by confidence descending
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         entities: Raw entity list from get_icd10_suggestions.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    235[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         List of suggestion dicts, each with:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m           code, description, score, source_text, traits
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    240[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     suggestions = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    242[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for entity in entities:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    243[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Check traits for negation. Comprehend Medical tags negated conditions
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    244[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # (like "denies chest pain") with a NEGATION trait. These should not
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    245[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # generate code suggestions for the negated condition.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    246[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         trait_names = [t["Name"] for t in entity.get("Traits", [])]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    247[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    248[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if "NEGATION" in trait_names:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             logger.debug("Skipping negated entity: %s", entity.get("Text", ""))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    251[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    252[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Process each ICD-10 code candidate for this entity.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    253[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # A single entity like "diabetes with kidney disease" might map to
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    254[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # multiple codes: E11.22 (combination), E11.9 (general), N18.9 (CKD alone).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    255[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for concept in entity.get("ICD10CMConcepts", []):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    256[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             score = concept.get("Score", 0.0)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    257[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    258[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if score < CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    259[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    260[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             suggestions.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "code": concept["Code"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "description": concept["Description"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "score": score,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "source_text": entity.get("Text", ""),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "traits": trait_names,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    267[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    268[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    269[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Deduplicate: same code can appear from multiple text spans.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    270[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Keep the instance with the highest confidence score.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    271[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     seen_codes = {}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    272[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for s in suggestions:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    273[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         code = s["code"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    274[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if code not in seen_codes or s["score"] > seen_codes[code]["score"]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    275[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             seen_codes[code] = s
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    276[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    277[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     deduped = sorted(seen_codes.values(), key=lambda x: x["score"], reverse=True)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    278[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Filtered to %d unique code suggestions", len(deduped))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    279[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return deduped
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    280[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    281[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    282[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    283[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    284[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 4: Apply Coding Rules and Specificity Logic
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    285[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    286[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *Maps to the pseudocode's `apply_coding_rules(suggestions, rules_table)`. Raw ML output doesn't understand ICD-10 coding guidelines. This step enforces specificity (suppress unspecified codes when a more specific code is present), checks for combination code opportunities, and flags excludes conflicts for human review. In production, these rules are maintained by your coding compliance team in DynamoDB. Here we use a static dictionary for illustration.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    287[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    288[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    289[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Static coding rules for demonstration. In production, load these from DynamoDB
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    290[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # so your compliance team can update them without code deployments.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    291[0m:[38;5;10m[49m SPECIFICITY_RULES = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    292[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # If a more specific code from this family is present, suppress the general one.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    293[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Format: general_code -> list of codes that supersede it.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    294[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "E11.9": ["E11.65", "E11.22", "E11.21", "E11.311", "E11.319", "E11.40", "E11.41"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    295[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "I10": ["I11.0", "I11.9", "I12.0", "I12.9", "I13.0", "I13.10"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    296[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "N18.9": ["N18.1", "N18.2", "N18.3", "N18.4", "N18.5", "N18.6"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    297[0m:[38;5;10m[49m }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    298[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    299[0m:[38;5;10m[49m COMBINATION_CODES = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    300[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # When both component conditions are documented, suggest the combination code.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    301[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Format: (condition_a_pattern, condition_b_pattern, combined_code, description)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    302[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     (
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    303[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "E11",   # diabetes type 2 (any specificity)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    304[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "N18",   # chronic kidney disease (any specificity)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    305[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "E11.22",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    306[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "Type 2 diabetes mellitus with diabetic chronic kidney disease",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    307[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    308[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     (
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    309[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "I11",   # hypertensive heart disease
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    310[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "N18",   # chronic kidney disease
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    311[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "I13.10",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    312[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "Hypertensive heart and chronic kidney disease without heart failure, with CKD stage 1-4",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    313[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    314[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    315[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    316[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    317[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def apply_coding_rules(suggestions: list) -> list:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    318[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    319[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Apply ICD-10 coding guidelines to the suggestion list.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    320[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    321[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This enforces three types of rules:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    322[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       1. Specificity: suppress general codes when specific alternatives are present
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    323[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       2. Combination codes: suggest combined codes when component conditions coexist
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    324[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       3. Excludes flags: mark code pairs that can't coexist (for human review)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    325[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    326[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    327[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         suggestions: Deduplicated, sorted suggestion list from filter_and_score.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    328[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    329[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    330[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Refined suggestion list with suppressed codes removed and flags added.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    331[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    332[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     active_codes = {s["code"] for s in suggestions}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    333[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    334[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # --- Specificity suppression ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    335[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     suppressed = set()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    336[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for general_code, specific_codes in SPECIFICITY_RULES.items():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    337[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if general_code in active_codes:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    338[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Check if any more specific sibling is also present
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    339[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             for specific in specific_codes:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    340[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 if specific in active_codes:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    341[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     suppressed.add(general_code)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    342[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     logger.info(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    343[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         "Suppressing %s (less specific than %s)", general_code, specific
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    344[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    345[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     break
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    346[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    347[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # --- Combination codes ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    348[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     combo_additions = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    349[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for pattern_a, pattern_b, combo_code, combo_desc in COMBINATION_CODES:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    350[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         has_a = any(c.startswith(pattern_a) for c in active_codes)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    351[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         has_b = any(c.startswith(pattern_b) for c in active_codes)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    352[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    353[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if has_a and has_b and combo_code not in active_codes:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    354[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             combo_additions.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    355[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "code": combo_code,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    356[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "description": combo_desc,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    357[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "score": 0.75,  # synthetic confidence for rule-derived suggestions
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    358[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "source_text": "(combination code: coding guideline)",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    359[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "traits": ["DIAGNOSIS"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    360[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "flags": ["combination_code"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    361[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    362[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             logger.info("Added combination code %s", combo_code)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    363[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    364[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Build final list: remove suppressed, add combos, preserve order.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    365[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     filtered = [s for s in suggestions if s["code"] not in suppressed]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    366[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    367[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Add flags field to existing suggestions if not present
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    368[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for s in filtered:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    369[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if "flags" not in s:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    370[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             s["flags"] = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    371[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    372[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     filtered.extend(combo_additions)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    373[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    374[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Re-sort by score and trim to max
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    375[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     filtered.sort(key=lambda x: x["score"], reverse=True)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    376[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return filtered[:MAX_SUGGESTIONS]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    377[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    378[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    379[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    380[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    381[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 5: Store Results and Build Response
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    382[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    383[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *Maps to the pseudocode's `store_and_respond(encounter_id, suggestions, original_note_length)`. The final step persists suggestions for audit trail and feedback collection, then returns the ranked list to the caller. Every suggestion includes its source text so the coder can see exactly what triggered it. DynamoDB requires Decimal for numbers (not float), which is why we wrap scores here.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    384[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    385[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    386[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def store_and_respond(encounter_id: str, suggestions: list, note_char_count: int) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    387[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    388[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Persist suggestion results to DynamoDB and build the API response.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    389[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    390[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Storing results serves three purposes:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    391[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       1. Audit trail: HIPAA requires you can show what the system suggested
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    392[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       2. Feedback loop: coders accept/reject codes, creating training labels
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    393[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       3. Analytics: track suggestion accuracy over time by encounter type
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    394[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    395[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    396[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         encounter_id: Unique identifier for the clinical encounter.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    397[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         suggestions: Final ranked suggestion list from apply_coding_rules.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    398[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         note_char_count: Character count of the original (pre-processed) note.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    399[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    400[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    401[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Response dict matching the API Gateway response format.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    402[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    403[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     timestamp = datetime.datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    404[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    405[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response_payload = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    406[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "encounter_id": encounter_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    407[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "timestamp": timestamp,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    408[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "note_char_count": note_char_count,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    409[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "suggestion_count": len(suggestions),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    410[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "suggestions": suggestions,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    411[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    412[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    413[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Write to DynamoDB. Scores must be Decimal, not float.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    414[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # boto3 raises TypeError on plain Python floats in DynamoDB items.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    415[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     table = dynamodb.Table(SUGGESTIONS_TABLE)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    416[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    417[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     dynamo_item = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    418[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "encounter_id": encounter_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    419[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "timestamp": timestamp,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    420[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "note_char_count": note_char_count,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    421[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "suggestion_count": len(suggestions),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    422[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "suggestions": json.loads(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    423[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             json.dumps(suggestions), parse_float=Decimal
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    424[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    425[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # TTL: retain for 90 days for feedback collection, then auto-expire.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    426[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "ttl": int(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    427[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             (datetime.datetime.now(timezone.utc) + datetime.timedelta(days=90)).timestamp()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    428[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    429[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    430[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    431[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     table.put_item(Item=dynamo_item)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    432[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    433[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "Stored %d suggestions for encounter %s", len(suggestions), encounter_id
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    434[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    435[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    436[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return response_payload
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    437[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    438[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    439[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    440[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    441[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Full Pipeline: Putting It All Together
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    442[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    443[0m:[38;5;10m[49m This assembles all steps into a single callable function. In a Lambda deployment, this is your handler's core logic. The Lambda receives the encounter ID and note text from API Gateway, runs the pipeline, and returns the suggestion JSON.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    444[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    445[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    446[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def suggest_icd10_codes(encounter_id: str, clinical_note: str) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    447[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    448[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     End-to-end ICD-10 code suggestion pipeline.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    449[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    450[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Takes a raw clinical note and returns ranked ICD-10-CM code suggestions.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    451[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is what your Lambda handler calls after extracting parameters from
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    452[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     the API Gateway event.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    453[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    454[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    455[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         encounter_id: Unique encounter identifier (from the EHR system).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    456[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         clinical_note: Raw clinical note text.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    457[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    458[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    459[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Dict with encounter metadata and ranked code suggestions.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    460[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    461[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"[1/5] Preprocessing note for encounter {encounter_id}...")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    462[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"       Original length: {len(clinical_note)} characters")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    463[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     processed_text = preprocess_note(clinical_note)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    464[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"       Processed length: {len(processed_text)} characters")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    465[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    466[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"[2/5] Calling Comprehend Medical InferICD10CM...")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    467[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     entities = get_icd10_suggestions(processed_text)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    468[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"       Received {len(entities)} entities")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    469[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    470[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"[3/5] Filtering and scoring suggestions...")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    471[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     suggestions = filter_and_score(entities)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    472[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"       {len(suggestions)} candidates after filtering")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    473[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    474[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"[4/5] Applying coding rules...")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    475[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     refined = apply_coding_rules(suggestions)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    476[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"       {len(refined)} suggestions after rules")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    477[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    478[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"[5/5] Storing results...")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    479[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     result = store_and_respond(encounter_id, refined, len(clinical_note))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    480[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"       Done. {result['suggestion_count']} suggestions returned.")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    481[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    482[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return result
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    483[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    484[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    485[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # --- Example usage with synthetic data ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    486[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    487[0m:[38;5;10m[49m if __name__ == "__main__":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    488[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Synthetic clinical note. This is NOT real patient data.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    489[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # It demonstrates the kind of text the system processes:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    490[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # an endocrinology follow-up with multiple active conditions.
